\par }{\f1\fs18 
\par Each label displays text set either by its configuration or dynamically by a }{\f1\fs18\uldb bang command}{\v\f1\fs18 BangCommands}{\f1\fs18 . The text can have a variety of fonts, sizes, colors and styles; it 
can also be shadowed. The following commands must be placed in the Litestep configuration file (step.rc). See the Litestep documentation for help modifying this file.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelFont}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 name}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the name of the font used to display text. If no value is provided then the default is Arial.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs18\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {LabelFontBold
