\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs16\super K}{ LabelImage;LabelImageLeftEdge;LabelImageTopEdge;LabelImageRightEdge;LabelImageBottomEdge;LabelImageMode}
}}{\b\f27 Changing a Label's Skin
\par }{\f1\fs18 
\par By default, labels are displayed with a simple solid gray background, but they also support }{\i\f1\fs18 skins}{\f1\fs18  (customizable bitmap-based interfaces). Label.dll uses the same skinning method used by two of my previou
s modules: systray.dll and chronos.dll. Basically, you provide a single bitmap that will be stretched or tiled to fill the background of the label. The problem is that sometimes this causes the edges of the bitmap to become distorted; To solve the problem
, label.dll supports }{\i\f1\fs18 edge scaling}{\f1\fs18 
, which allows you to set the number of pixels on each edge of the bitmap that will not be stretched or tiled. The following commands must be placed in the Litestep configuration file (step.rc). See the Litestep documentation for help modifying this file.

\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImage}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 filename}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the name of the skin file which must be in Windows bitmap (BMP) format. If no value is provided then the label is displayed with the default solid gray background.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImageLeftEdge}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 number}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the number of pixels on the left edge of the bitmap that will not be stretched or tiled. If no value is provided then the default is 0.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImageTopEdge}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 number}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the number of pixels on the top edge of the bitmap that will not be stretched or tiled. If no value is provided then the default is 0.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImageRightEdge}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 number}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the number of pixels on the right edge of the bitmap that will not be stretched or tiled. If no value is provided then the default is 0.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImageBottomEdge}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 number}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the number of pixels on the bottom edge of the bitmap that will not be stretched or tiled. If no value is provided then the default is 0.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelImageMode}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 "stretch", "tile", "tileHorizontal", or "tileVertical"}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets the method used to scale to skin. If none is provided then the default is stretch.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelTransparent}{\f1\fs18 
\par If this command is present then it enables transparency. If a skin is also in use then areas of the skin bitmap that are pink (RGB 255, 0, 255) will allow the desktop wallpaper to show through. If no skin is in use and this command is present then the 
entire label will be transparent.
\par 
