\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs16\super $}{ Events}}K{\footnote \pard\plain 
\s15\ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\cs16\super K}{ LabelOnLeftClick;LabelOnLeftDoubleClick;LabelOnMiddleClick;L
abelOnMiddleDoubleClick;LabelOnRightClick;LabelOnRightDoubleClick;LabelOnMouseEnter;LabelOnMouseLeave}}}{\b\f27 Events
\par }{\f1\fs18 
\par Labels can execute custom actions for various mouse events to enable you to create more interactive themes. All of the following commands accept a
 program or bang command which will be executed when the corresponding event occurs. For the mouse click events, only use either the single click version or the double click version but not both. The following commands must be placed in the Litestep confi
guration file (step.rc). See the Litestep documentation for help modifying this file.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnLeftClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user left clicks the label.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnLeftDoubleClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user double-clicks the label with the left mouse button.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnMiddleClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user middle clicks the label.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnMiddleDoubleClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user double-clicks the label with the middle mouse button.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnRightClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user right clicks the label.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnRightDoubleClick}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the user double-clicks the label with the right mouse button.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnMouseEnter}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the mouse cursor enters the label.
\par 
\par }{\b\f1\fs18 LabelOnMouseLeave}{\f1\fs18  }{\i\f1\fs18 action}{\f1\fs18 
\par Sets an action to perform when the mouse cursor leaves the label.
\par 
\par 
